      <div class="msgContentFrame"> <br />Depends on the situation. <br /> <br />In Party i would imagine casting on this order. <br />Silence if the mob is mage type. <br />Dia (if the mob hits weak but strong defense) or Bio (if the mob has weak def but strong attack), select 1. <br />Slow to make the mob attack less the tank, <br />Paralyze to make the mob attack less <br />Blind Make the mob accuracy down <br />Absorb EVA/ATK/DEF are next to cast <br />Sacrifice for extra healing and regen. <br />Gravity if the mob always runs away or for links. <br /> <br />Of course some of those spells are not in your level yet, so just ignore them until you have it. <br />I think prioritizing accuracy before potency is always a good path.  <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Mikayla Soulfire (XIV), Ul'dah, Istory <br /><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2218114" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2218114">Lodestone Profile</a> <br /> <br />Mikael (XI) Bastok, CaithSith <br />RDM/BST/BLU/NIN/BLM <br /> <br />Thus is our agreement written, thus is treaty made. Thought is the arrow of time; Memory never fades. What was asked is given; The price is paid.</div></div>
