      <div class="msgContentFrame">I have most of my support spells (sacrifice/cure/siphon MP/etc) on my second bar and have these macro'd. The hot bar has my spells d'jour depending on what I am fighting and if im in party/duo/solo etc. This works for my level atm but it will change im sure. Its one thing to note that if you want to try and get maximum SP from your party being extra nasty to the mob isnt always the best tactic. Making the mob hit for less or hit less often means less heals which means less SP. So what I tend to go for is a spell set in a party that weakens the mobs to some degree but still enables it to hit the tank/etc for a decent amount so I can heal. Only when I hit cap do I want to take it down asap. Again in a party situation this will depend on my other party members and what they are cool with.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
