      <div class="msgContentFrame">1 Spirit Dart  <br />2 Poison  <br />3 Dia or Bio depending on what im doing <br />4 Sacrifice   <br />5 Cure (from Conjurer)  <br />6 Guard  <br />7 Shock Spikes (Conjurer)  <br />8 Stoneskin (Conjurer)  <br />9 Slow <br />0 Exaltation  <br /> <br />I also have the same setup on my CTR Macro bar with Sac/Cure set up to auto target me and the attack type spells to /aoe off hit my target ie.... <br /> <br />Ctrl 2 <br />/aoe off <br />/ac &quot;Poison&quot; &lt;t&gt; <br /> <br />Ctrl 5 <br />/aoe off <br />/ac &quot;cure&quot; &lt;me&gt; <br /> <br />By doing this you can cast with out all of the incessant clicking. Initially I didnt have the /aoe off line but every once in a while it would bug so I added that and now have no issue. I also have Gravity in place of sacrifice on my Ctrl macro tab. As long as they are somewhere on your bars(Even on the second line), you can add them to a macro <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1821254.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
